cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SI, cs.DS

The paper discusses the use of Long Short-Term Memory networks trained with gradient descent and back-propagation, which are commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence applications. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes an algorithm for outlier detection, which falls under the category of anomaly detection, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) likely sub-categories as well. Finally, the paper uses maximum likelihood estimation, which is a statistical method, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) a possible sub-category.
